# Configuration CAPITUNE

## Frontend (.env.local)

```env
# API
NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://localhost:3001
NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_NAME=CAPITUNE

# Analytics (optional)
NEXT_PUBLIC_SENTRY_DSN=
NEXT_PUBLIC_MIXPANEL_TOKEN=

# Auth
NEXT_PUBLIC_AUTH_STORAGE_KEY=capitune_auth_token
```

## Backend (.env)

```env
# Server
NODE_ENV=development
PORT=3001

# Database
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://user:password@localhost:5432/capitune
DATABASE_POOL_SIZE=10

# Auth
JWT_SECRET=your-super-secret-jwt-key-change-in-prod
JWT_EXPIRY=1h
REFRESH_TOKEN_EXPIRY=30d

# Email (Sendgrid)
SENDGRID_API_KEY=SG.xxx
SENDGRID_FROM_EMAIL=noreply@capitune.com

# File Storage (AWS S3)
AWS_REGION=ca-central-1
AWS_S3_BUCKET=capitune-files
AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=xxx
AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=xxx

# SMS (Twilio - V2)
TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID=
TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN=
TWILIO_PHONE_NUMBER=

# Cache (Redis)
REDIS_URL=redis://localhost:6379

# Logging
LOG_LEVEL=info

# Monitoring (Sentry)
SENTRY_DSN=

# CORS
CORS_ORIGIN=http://localhost:3000
```

## Docker (.env pour docker-compose)

```env
# PostgreSQL
POSTGRES_USER=capitune
POSTGRES_PASSWORD=dev-password-123
POSTGRES_DB=capitune

# Redis
REDIS_PASSWORD=dev-password-123
```

---

**Utilisation** :

- **Frontend** : `frontend/.env.local` (ne pas committer)
- **Backend** : `backend/.env` (ne pas committer)
- **Docker** : `.env` à la racine (docker-compose)

---

**Checklist de sécurité** :

✅ Changer tous les secrets en production
✅ Utiliser secrets manager (AWS Secrets Manager, Heroku Config Vars)
✅ Ne pas committer .env
✅ Rotation tokens régulièrement (V2)
